Sunday Ehigiator Bona Expo 22, a pioneer exposition for Green Beauty Manufacturers in Africa, Africans-In-the-diaspora, and a selected few internationals looking to gain entrance into the continent, has been scheduled to hold on March 30, and 31, to change the course of green beauty in Africa. In a statement over the weekend, from the organisers, the two-day event themed, ‘Mother Nature Africa’ is a botanical, organic, and Natural Africa Expo, which has spotlighted its vendor interests from countries like Nigeria, Ghana, Kenya, South Africa, Namibia, Uganda, Uk, Canada & USA. “The Botanical, Organic and Natural Africa Expo has spotlighted its vendor interests from countries like Nigeria, Ghana, Kenya, South Africa, Namibia, Uganda, Uk, Canada & USA. “Bona Expo 22, two-day exposition will hold on Wednesday, Thursday, March 30 and 31, 2022 at The Landmark Centre, 3&4 Water Corporation, Oniru, Victoria Island Lagos, Nigeria. “It will feature activities such as the welcome dinner, exhibitions and unique experiences, and masterclasses by international speakers, panel discussions, to wrap-up-party. “The objective is to actively engage and immerse the Green Beauty Industry and its Stakeholders in a quality, value-adding, and indelible brand experience. “Sensitize the public on the choice and importance of clean and safe living driving ultimately our sustainability program. Re-establish our natural ingredients as a part of tangible African heritage, therefore, driving and creating policies to its effect. “Promote thought-leadership agenda and positioning for the Green Beauty Industry in Africa and her African Manufacturers as well as increase opportunities for more entrants into the Industry and Continent. “Drive sustainable conversations around African organic and natural Beauty Industry in the hope that it sensitizes the discontinued use of chemical-based products.”